1. In these Terms of Use (as defined below) the following definitions shall apply:
  1.1. “IOGP” means the International Association of Oil and Gas Producers, incorporated in England as a company limited by guarantee (number 1832064);
  1.2. “GIGS” means the Geospatial Integrity of Geoscience Software testing framework, published by IOGP, incorporating the GIGS Software;
  1.3. “GIGS Software” means the associated elements and contributions of the GIGS framework, including but not limited to: the GIGS Website, the GIGS Test Dataset files, the GIGS Test Series files and the GIGS Documentation;
  1.4. “GIGS Website” means the online portal serving all GIGS Software hosted by IOGP and currently available at https://www.gigs.iogp.org;
  1.5. “GIGS Test Dataset” means the collection of files that contain reference data and source code associated with GIGS Tests;
  1.6. “GIGS Test Series” means the compilation of recommended GIGS Tests pertaining to specific technical themes, as recommended by IOGP;
  1.7. “GIGS Tests” means the specific procedures that involve testing certain functions within a digital application;
  1.8. “GIGS Documentation” means the reports published by IOGP associated with undertaking a GIGS Evaluation;
  1.9. “GIGS Evaluation” means the process of executing GIGS testing and applying all/some of the GIGS Software to a specific digital application in order to generate a GIGS Score; and
  1.10. “GIGS Score” means the calculated level and percentage score that determines the level of conformance of the digital application being tested; and
  1.11. "Terms of Use" means these terms and conditions governing the use of the GIGS Software and GIGS Website.

2. The GIGS Software are published via the GIGS Website by IOGP at no charge. Distribution for profit is forbidden. The GIGS Software and GIGS Website remain proprietary to IOGP.

3. The GIGS Software components are compiled by the GIGS User Group, of IOPG, from publicly available and IOGP member-supplied information.

4. The GIGS Test Dataset is comprised entirely of synthetic data generated for testing purposes only and any resemblance to “real world” or otherwise proprietary datasets is purely coincidental. The selection of geodetic entities within the GIGS Test Dataset is designed to be as wide-ranging as possible and does not represent IOGPs interest, affiliation or alignment with any particular organisation or geography.

